---
import { Github, Linkedin, Mail } from 'lucide-astro';
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="Learn more about Bart Kessels, software developer and outdoor enthusiast.">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    {/* Header */}
    <header class="mb-12 text-center">
      <div class="w-32 h-32 mx-auto mb-6 rounded-full bg-muted overflow-hidden">
        <img
          src="/images/avatar.jpg"
          alt="Bart Kessels"
          class="w-full h-full object-cover"
        />
      </div>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-foreground mb-4">Bart Kessels</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-muted">Software Developer & Outdoor Enthusiast</p>
    </header>

    {/* Bio */}
    <section class="prose max-w-none mb-12">
      <p>
        Hi! I'm Bart, a software developer based in the Netherlands. I'm passionate about creating 
        clean, maintainable software and exploring the great outdoors.
      </p>

      <h2>What I Do</h2>
      <p>
        By day, I work as a software developer focusing on C# and .NET applications. I enjoy solving 
        complex problems and building tools that make developers' lives easier.
      </p>
      <p>
        In my spare time, I contribute to open source projects, explore Android and Kotlin development, 
        and tinker with native Linux applications using GTK.
      </p>

      <h2>Beyond Code</h2>
      <p>
        When I'm not coding, you'll find me either on a hiking trail with my backpack or in my 
        vegetable garden. I believe in balancing screen time with time in nature.
      </p>
      <p>
        Backpacking has taught me patience, planning, and the importance of traveling light - 
        lessons that surprisingly apply well to software development too.
      </p>

      <h2>This Blog</h2>
      <p>
        I started this blog to share what I learn along the way. Whether it's a tricky CMake 
        configuration, a beautiful hiking route, or tips for growing tomatoes in a Dutch climate - 
        if I found it useful, maybe you will too.
      </p>
    </section>

    {/* Social Links */}
    <section class="border-t border-border pt-8">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-6 text-center">Get in Touch</h2>
      <div class="flex items-center justify-center gap-6">
        <a
          href="https://github.com/bartkessels"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg border border-border hover:border-accent hover:bg-accent/5 transition-all text-muted hover:text-foreground"
        >
          <Github class="h-5 w-5" />
          GitHub
        </a>
        <a
          href="https://linkedin.com/in/bartkessels"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg border border-border hover:border-accent hover:bg-accent/5 transition-all text-muted hover:text-foreground"
        >
          <Linkedin class="h-5 w-5" />
          LinkedIn
        </a>
        <a
          href="mailto:hello@bartkessels.net"
          class="flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg border border-border hover:border-accent hover:bg-accent/5 transition-all text-muted hover:text-foreground"
        >
          <Mail class="h-5 w-5" />
          Email
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
